{"article_id":"V6vjWYHESjKNv1xX","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"It ' s not true that the government shutdown ,","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"concluded over the weekend after 35 days of shutdown ,","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"accomplished \" nothing. \"","depth":2},{"id":3,"text":"President Trump did not score a policy victory on the issue","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"that led to the shutdown .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"The continuing resolution","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"that is to run for three weeks ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"as signed by the president ,","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"does not include a dime of funding for a wall along the U.S.-Mexican border .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"The Mexican standoff over the Mexican border wall did , however , accomplish something important .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"It revealed","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"just how radical the Democrats have become on the issue of immigration .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"In the run-up to the 2020 election elections , they have been smoked out .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"That ' s not nothing .","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"The telling fact ,","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"what will become clear over the next two years ,","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"was Democratic radicalism","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"that caused the shutdown in the first place .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"President Trump did not ask for much , just $ 5.7 billion","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"to begin construction of a barrier along porous sections of the border .","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"The sum of $ 5.7 billion seems like a lot to mere mortals ,","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"but it was no more than a rounding error against the largesse of the federal budget .","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"Not long ago , Democrats like Chuck Schumer and Hillary Clinton , happily voted to build barriers along the border .","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"The president ' s request can only be judged unreasonable by a campaign consultant","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"looking for an issue","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"to exploit .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"But something happened on the way","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"to striking a budget deal .","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"When faced with President Trump ' s demand for an appropriation for wall construction ,","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"Speaker of the House Nancy Pelosi , the party theologian , said","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"building the wall would be an \" immorality. \"","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"The Democrats ,","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"figuring","depth":14},{"id":33,"text":"that being against borders and national sovereignty , the building blocks of the nation state , would be winning politics ,","depth":14},{"id":34,"text":"boasted","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"they would never spend a penny on maintaining the border .","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"This was breathtakingly radical ,","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"and led directly to the shutdown","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"when the president rightly declined to go along .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"The shutdown did inflict damage .","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"Eight hundred thousand federal workers went weeks","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"without pay ,","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"though they will be paid for time missed .","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"Less fortunate contract workers , like those","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"who clean the restrooms at the Smithsonian Institution , for example ,","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"won ' t be .","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"During the shutdown , air traffic control and the TSA were hobbled .","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"National parks were closed .","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"Tax rebate checks will be delayed ,","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"given the backlog of work","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"that piled up during the shutdown .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"It ' s clear to everyone why the president felt compelled to end the shutdown , even at the cost of nothing for the wall .","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"In the face of Democratic intransigence , he took the responsible position .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"He couldn ' t negotiate a compromise with Democrats","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"who said","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"they would never compromise .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"There are two reasons , neither good .","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"The first is nakedly political .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"The central promise of Mr. Trump ' s 2016 campaign was building the wall .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"Denying him the ability","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"to do that","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"would damage his re-election campaign","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"by making the wall a broken promise .","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"The president ' s own political miscalculation played a part here .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"He should have asked for funding for the wall","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"when the Republicans controlled the House","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"instead of waiting","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"until Mrs. Pelosi took over .","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"The other reason is even more cynical .","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"Democrats claim","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"to oppose the wall","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"because \" it doesn ' t work. \"","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"This is nonsense .","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"The experience of San Diego , Israel and other places demonstrates","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"that walls work well .","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"If walls are not effective ,","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"why are they ,","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"as Mrs. Pelosi insists ,","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"\" immoral ? \"","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"In fact , the actual reason","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"Democrats oppose the border barrier","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"is precisely because walls do work .","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"With declining support from white and older Americans , the Democrats have concluded","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"that their future lies in importing a new electorate from south of the border .","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"A wall would prevent that .","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"The continuing resolution runs until Feb. 15 ,","depth":5},{"id":86,"text":"when there could very well be another shutdown .","depth":5},{"id":87,"text":"The Democrats are unlikely to capitulate .","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"Neither is the president .","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"Mr. Trump has floated another idea","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"to get his wall funding ,","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"declaring a national emergency","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"and order the wall to be built .","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"The president has the legal authority","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"to do so ,","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"though this option makes a lot of us uneasy .","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"Declaring a national emergency in the face of political intransigence would set a dangerous precedent .","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"The Democrats ,","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"by refusing to protect the country ' s sovereignty for nakedly political ends ,","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"are setting a dangerous precedent themselves .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":199,"left":102,"right":198,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":101,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":101,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":198,"left":149,"right":197,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":149,"left":116,"right":148,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":116,"left":107,"right":115,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":107,"left":103,"right":106,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":106,"left":105,"right":8,"